                    </div>
                    <div id="thematic-trace-p6-2026" class="thematic-trace">
                        <h4>Thematic Tracing:</h4>
                        <p><strong>Character-Driven Fantasy, Expansive Sci-Fi, and Foundational Afrofuturism:</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>The Sword of Kaigen: Character-driven military fantasy exploring sacrifice, family, and cultural expectations.</li>
                            <li>Children of Time Series (Ruin & Memory): Expansive, big-idea science fiction delving into alien intelligence, consciousness, and societal evolution.</li>
                            <li>Patternist Series: Foundational Afrofuturism by Octavia E. Butler, exploring power, eugenics, psionic abilities, and societal evolution over millennia.</li>
                            <li>The Sixth World Series: Indigenous futurism blending post-apocalyptic urban fantasy with Navajo mythology.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><em>Significance:</em> This phase offers profound epics for winter contemplation, including a major Butler series and explorations of unique cultural futurisms, transitioning into dynamic series as spring approaches.</p>
