                            <h3>Spring/Summer 2026: Diverse Voices & Expansive Worlds</h3>
                            <span class="phase-date">Late Apr - Aug 2026</span>
                        </div>
                        <button class="toggle-theme-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="thematic-trace-ss-2026">Show Themes ✨</button>
                    </div>
                    <div id="thematic-trace-ss-2026" class="thematic-trace">
                        <h4>Thematic Tracing:</h4>
                        <p><strong>Varied Cultural Futurisms, Gothic Horror, Epic Afrofantasy, and Climate Fiction:</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Lagoon: Chaotic first contact in Lagos, blending sci-fi with Nigerian mythology and social commentary.</li>
                            <li>Glass and Gardens: Solarpunk Summers: Optimistic visions of sustainable futures.</li>
                            <li>Mexican Gothic: Atmospheric Latinx Gothic horror critiquing power and patriarchy.</li>
                            <li>Dark Star Trilogy: Epic Afrofantasy drawing on African history and mythology, exploring unreliable narration.</li>
                            <li>Out There Screaming: New Black horror anthology.</li>
                            <li>The Ministry for the Future: Monumental climate fiction exploring global politics and resilience.</li>
                            <li>Never Whistle at Night: Indigenous dark fiction anthology.</li>
                            <li>Womb City: Inventive Africanfuturism exploring bodies as resources and consciousness transfer.</li>
                            <li>The Perfect Assassin: Adventure fantasy offering a potential palate cleanser or series binge.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><em>Significance:</em> This extended phase showcases a vibrant array of diverse voices and genres, from Afrofuturism and Solarpunk to Gothic horror and epic fantasy, reflecting the expansive possibilities of speculative fiction for spring and summer immersion.</p>
                    </div>
