                        <div>
                            <h3>Spring 2027: Foundational Voices & New Beginnings</h3>
                            <span class="phase-date">Mar - May 2027</span>
                        </div>
                        <button class="toggle-theme-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="thematic-trace-s-2027">Show Themes ✨</button>
                    </div>
                    <div id="thematic-trace-s-2027" class="thematic-trace">
                        <h4>Thematic Tracing:</h4>
                        <p><strong>Seminal Afrofuturism, Genre-Defining Epics, and Unique Cultural Futurisms:</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Earthseed Series: Foundational Afrofuturist works by Octavia E. Butler exploring societal rebuilding, faith, and resilience in a dystopian climate-changed future.</li>
                            <li>The Broken Earth Trilogy: Monumental sociopolitical sci-fi/fantasy by N.K. Jemisin, dealing with climate cataclysm, oppression, power, and survival.</li>
                            <li>Kindred: A profound Afrofuturist classic by Butler bridging past and present through the trauma of slavery.</li>
                            <li>The Lesson: Caribbean sci-fi exploring first contact, colonialism, and reconciliation.</li>
                            <li>Noor: Africanfuturist work by Nnedi Okorafor examining cyberpunk themes, corporate greed, and bodily autonomy.</li>
                            <li>Xenogenesis/Lilith's Brood Trilogy: Deeply philosophical Afrofuturism by Butler questioning humanity, consent, and genetic engineering.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><em>Significance:</em> This spring phase is anchored by foundational works from Octavia E. Butler and N.K. Jemisin, alongside innovative futurisms from other key voices, aligning with themes of transformation, resilience, and new beginnings.</p>
                    </div>
