                <div class="phase">
                    <div class="phase-header">
                        <div>
                            <h3>Summer 2027: Alien Encounters, Mythic Quests, & Dystopian Realities</h3>
                            <span class="phase-date">May - Aug 2027</span>
                        </div>
                        <button class="toggle-theme-btn" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="thematic-trace-su-2027">Show Themes ✨</button>
                    </div>
                    <div id="thematic-trace-su-2027" class="thematic-trace">
                        <h4>Thematic Tracing:</h4>
                        <p><strong>Complex Alien Worlds, Mythological Fantasies, and Indigenous Dystopias:</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Wormwood Trilogy: Afrofuturist biopunk series with alien invasion, telepathy, and unique world-building in Nigeria.</li>
                            <li>A Master of Djinn: Steampunk Afrofuturist mystery set in an alternate 1912 Cairo, rich with magic and djinn.</li>
                            <li>Gods of Jade and Shadow: Historical fantasy drawing on Mayan mythology in Jazz Age Mexico.</li>
                            <li>The Marrow Thieves Series: Poignant Indigenous dystopian YA exploring cultural survival and resilience.</li>
                            <li>Moon of the Crusted Snow Series: Indigenous post-apocalyptic narrative focusing on community and return to traditional ways.</li>
                            <li>Riot Baby & Death of the Author: Afrofuturist satire/social commentary and a major Okorafor work on art and identity.</li>
                            <li>House of Bone and Rain & The Haunting of Room 904: Latinx and Indigenous horror.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><em>Significance:</em> Summer offers immersive dives into complex alien worlds, captivating mythological quests, and powerful dystopian narratives from Indigenous and Afrofuturist perspectives, balanced with sharp social commentary and chilling horror.</p>
                    </div>
                    <article class="event-block">
                        <span class="event-block-date">May 17 - June 6, 2027 (3 weeks): SERIES BINGE</span>
                        <h4>Rosewater (Wormwood Trilogy #1) by Tade Thompson (13h 37m). Narrated by Bayo Gbadamosi.</h4>
                        <h4>The Rosewater Insurrection (Wormwood Trilogy #2) by Tade Thompson (approx. 13h). Narrated by Bayo Gbadamosi.</h4>
