                        <h4>Thematic Tracing:</h4>
                        <p><strong>Short Fiction, Reflection, and Flexible Exploration:</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>How Long ’Til Black Future Month?: Acclaimed short story collection by N.K. Jemisin, spanning fantasy, sci-fi, and horror, exploring Black and marginalized experiences.</li>
                            <li>Buffer Period & Flexibility: Allows for catching up, revisiting favorites, exploring newly released sequels (e.g., The Sixth World #3, Dark Star Trilogy #3), or discovering new titles.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><em>Significance:</em> This final phase offers a reflective culmination with a celebrated short story collection and provides flexibility to tailor the end of the journey to personal preferences and new releases, ensuring a satisfying conclusion to the multi-year odyssey.</p>
                    </div>
                    <article class="event-block">
                        <span class="event-block-date">November 15 - November 28, 2027 (2 weeks): Jemisin Short Fiction <span class="audio-tag tag-mc">(MC)</span><span class="audio-tag tag-pc">(PC)</span></span>
